1. Generally all HTML can be considered as Boxes
-It consist of four different parts of boxes - Outer box to Inner Box

a. Outer Box is (Margin)
b. first Inner Box is (Border)
c. Second Inner (Padding)
d. And central (Inner)

Content:
--------
Content of elements could be (Text) or (Images). We are able to manage it size using (Width) & (Height).

Padding
--------
This create an area around (content) and it's transparent . It is followed by

Border
------
This goes around (CONTENT) & (PADDING) .It is kind of wrapper for the by default border is invicible but we can define its style
(WIDTH) & (COLOR) Using CSS Properties

MARGIN
-------
This clears an area outside the Border like MARGIN,PADDING is also transparent